x4freetext: -the TACO experiment for the determination of
integral cross sections in a fast reactor.-
spectrum is given in table 2 of the 82ANTWER,175,1982
.Each nuclide to be irradiated was dissolved
in nitric acid. Aliquots of the solutions were
placed in thin-walled aluminium capsules and
dried under vacuum. The nitrates were then
decomposed by heating. The capsules were closed
under vacuum and collapsed when atmospheric
pressure was restored. The capsules were
folded and placed in stainless steel cans of
4.3 mm outer diameter and 30 mm length which
were in turn sealed by electron beam welding.
before and after a long irradiation were
determined by using a mass spectrometer.
therefore a non irradiated sample was kept
.Interferences due to natural background from the
filament. Corrections were applied based on
selected masses, naturally abundant but depleted
done twice to estimate the measurement errors.
